Bring the charm of early 20th-century America to your tabletop with this beautifully crafted Small Town STL Set, designed by InfinitePrint 3D and now available under official license on Proxywars.

Inspired by real architecture from 1900s small-town America, this set captures the essence of a bygone era, from corner barbershops and bakeries to classic brick facades and streetlamp-lined sidewalks. Whether you're staging a noir-style narrative, building a diorama, or expanding your wargaming terrain, these models are a perfect fit for historical, pulp, or modern alternate history settings.

A set of modular walls and roofs intended to make a wide variety of 8mm scale buildings - warehouses, hangars, worker barracks, etc. Designed in a simple, pre-fab style intended to give a look of quickly churned out industrial buildings.

Please bear in mind that due to the nature of the pieces and their fit, some sanding/filing will almost always be necessary for proper fit.

Set includes 10 different mid-height walls, 7 high (double the size of mid), 5 roof, some support pieces for joining the straight sections and one double wide section each of mid and high wall.

I`ve test printed on Anycubic Photon Mono 2 at 35 micron layer height. Results are on the photos.

I strongly suggest first trying those free test pieces to see if you can get acceptable results from your printer:
https://cults3d.com/en/3d-model/game/imperial-cellarion-8mm-test-pieces

This is a set for creating a city building as a terrain for any wargame in 1/285 (6mm) scale. The set allows you to assemble both an intact (undamaged) buildings and a destroyed ones (ruins). You can assemble a building of any height you want by printing the required number of intermediate floors.


There is one option with square windows (marked with number 1) and the second with rounded windows (marked with number 2).


To make it easier to paint the windows, I made it a separate piece that can be painted in advance (for example, with spray paint) and inserted inside the walls.


I also made a set of interior parts in case you don't use windows or want to make glass from transparent material.

A pair of simple retro-style sci fi cactuses for tabletop RPGs and wargames.

I designed these for a 15mm scale project I'm working on, for which I print them at 50% scale. These are scaled to be 40mm and 60mm (ish) tall when printed at 100%, so would work for 28mm-32mm scale miniatures. However, they are intentionally simple and chunky, both to have they retro feel and to work when scaled down. They should work at anything down to 25% scale, if you fancied some spikey plants for your 8mm games!

Great for retro themed grim dark scifi terrain, for games such as 40k, SW Legions, etc.

Please see my other models and consider donating.

Thanks!

This is a collection of many gothic sci-fi buildings, for 6mm / 1:285 gaming - primarily Battletech and Epic.

The buildings are combinations of tower blocks that equate to level 1, 2 and 3 for when used within Battletech. There are two types of roof, flat and peeked as well as some other embellishments which means all up there are 290 different buildings in this set, although they're all different combinations of tower blocks.

For Battletech, they are designed to fit entirely within the "standard" Battletech map hexes of 33mm flat edge to flat edge as is used in the current boxed sets. The flat roof versions are also designed to allow Mech models to be placed on them.

The models are designed to be mostly supportless on an FDM printer and have printed fine on my Ender 3.

If you'd like any combination of the towers that isn't currently present, let me know and I'll create it and add it in.

There's a couple of the buildings over on thingiverse if you'd like to try printing them [https://www.thingiverse.com/thing:4691171](https://www.thingiverse.com/thing:4691171).
